<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1438">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>977. This Government will undertake the work requested by the British
                            Government in your 1474 in accordance with the plan outlined in the
                            Department’s 963 of yesterday, and <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Gerard</persName> has been instructed to present the matter to the
                            German Government and report.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>